tir the icing. It will not look like enough moisture until you have it all stirred up (the sugar sort of melts into it). If it is still too thick/stiff, juice the other half of the lemon. You want the icing thick but still loose enough to drizzle over the scones.", "When the scones are golden brown on top, remove them from the oven and let cool. Be sure to let the scones cool before adding the icing or else it will melt and slide right off!."], "images": [{"url": "http://lh5.ggpht.com/_OaYG005JPDs/TGA3q9jdKZI/AAAAAAAABrI/6dAqjUtS4ZU/s640/Blueberry%20Scone%20plate.jpg", "path": "full/70722448a0ab2a49590966c95999845e26b2c79e.jpg", "checksum": "5212030fa9a6fe680548be8f8a10589e"}], "link": "http://www.budgetbytes.com/2010/08/lemon-blueberry-scones/", "recipe_cook_time": ["PT15M"], "recipe_yield": ["8"]}